===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} {{term|thagh|thagh, thaugh||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|þeah|þēah|lang=ang}}, later superseded in many dialects by {{etyl|enm}} {{term|though|thogh, though||lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|non}} *{{term||þóh}} (later {{term|þó}}), both from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|þauh||though|lang=gem-pro}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|to-|lang=ine-pro}}. Akin to {{etyl|ofs|-}} {{term|þah|þāh||lang=ofs}} "though", {{etyl|osx|-}} {{term|þoh|þōh||though|lang=osx}}, {{nl}} {{term|doch|doch||lang=nl}}, {{etyl|goh|-}} {{term|doh|dōh||though, but, yet, nevertheless|lang=goh}} ({{de}} {{term|doch|doch|lang=de}}). More at [[that]].

